# Repository & Git safety

- Work from a normal local clone. If the checkout lives inside a syncing folder
  (iCloud Drive, Dropbox, etc.), STOP and report a relocation plan first.
- Do NOT commit, push, merge, rebase, cherry-pick, reset, force-push, delete branches,
  drop stashes, or rewrite Git history unless the current task explicitly authorizes it.
- Preserve all existing files and uncommitted work. Never discard local changes.
- Inspect (`git status`, diff) before changing anything. Prefer minimal, scoped diffs.
- Never modify autogenerated Alembic migration files by hand.
- `.ai/` and `.cursor/rules/` are version-controlled governance (safe to track).
- Treat `HANDOFF.md`, `CHANGELOG_SESSION.md`, and `*.local.md` as gitignored; never stage them.
